latestPosts.caption: They all called me at once... so I used my baby brains 🧠💡 Went to Mumma first (obviously ❤️), then Papa 👨‍👦, then Masi 🫶 — no hurt feelings, just spreading the love one step at a time! 👣💕 #SmartBabyMoves #ILoveYouAll #PrioritiesInOrder"

One year of love, laughter, and divine blessings.
We celebrated our little one’s 1st birthday at the sacred Rameshwaram Jyotirling — a place of peace and powerful blessings.
This past year, I’ve found myself visiting many spiritual places, and I truly believe it’s my baby who brought this divine journey into my life.
Grateful beyond words for the joy, the lessons, and the light he has brought into our world.🙏
Thank you, my little one @devansh_nayak1178😘 , for making life more meaningful 💫

latestPosts.caption:
Brihadeshwar temple, Thanjavur 
One of the largest temples in India built by King Rajaraja chola in the 11th century,It is also known as Big temple as the temple tower is 216 ft high and the tallest of its kind in the world.
The main attraction of this temple is the top stone which is a single stone of 80 tonnes , the big statue of Nandi and a Huge Shiva lingam.
A UNESCO world heritage site.
.
.
